=========================================================
INHERITANCE IN C++ (INTERVIEW NOTES)
=========================================================

Definition:
Inheritance is an OOP mechanism in which one class (Derived Class)
acquires the properties and behaviors (data members and member
functions) of another class (Base Class).

In simple words:

Existing Class
       ↓
Reuse in New Class
       ↓
Inheritance

=========================================================
WHY DO WE NEED INHERITANCE?
=========================================================

Without Inheritance:
• Code duplication
• Difficult maintenance
• Less reusability
• More bugs

Inheritance provides:
• Code Reusability
• Extensibility
• Better Maintenance
• Reduced Redundancy
• Runtime Polymorphism support

=========================================================
BASIC SYNTAX
=========================================================

class Base
{
};

class Derived : public Base
{
};

=========================================================
EXAMPLE
=========================================================

#include <iostream>
using namespace std;

class Animal
{
public:
    void eat()
    {
        cout << "Eating\n";
    }
};

class Dog : public Animal
{
public:
    void bark()
    {
        cout << "Barking\n";
    }
};

int main()
{
    Dog d;

    d.eat();
    d.bark();
}

Output:

Eating
Barking

