=========================================================

Inheritance is one of the four pillars of OOP and is a mechanism by
which a derived class acquires the properties and behaviors of a base
class. It promotes code reuse, extensibility, and supports runtime
polymorphism. Inheritance represents an IS-A relationship and should be
used only when a true parent-child relationship exists. Otherwise,
Composition (HAS-A relationship) is generally preferred.

